The St Mary's outfit are understood to be pursuing both Spurs wing Andros Townsend and unsettled Atletico Madrid defender Toby Alderweireld.

Saints take on Championship club Millwall in the Capital One Cup on Tuesday night, with Koeman keen to see his side fire back to finishing form.

'I think sometimes he can be a little bit more aggressive maybe, to expect in which position the ball falls down,' Koeman told the Southern Daily Echo of Pelle, Saints' Italian summer recruit from Feyenoord.

'But he needs players from the midfield and with movements around him. If there comes a long ball, you have to expect something. If you wait and you go then, sometimes you are too late.'

Tadic joined Saints from FC Twente in the summer, recruited to replace Liverpool-bound Adam Lallana. 

